article.headline: Kennesaw State 80, Jacksonville St. 74
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Shuan Stegall scored 19 points and grabbed 12 rebounds and freshman Tanner Jacobs added 18 points to lead Kennesaw State to an 80-74 victory over Jacksonville State to advance to the finals of the 100 Club Classic on Friday night. The victory sends the Owls (1-2) to Saturday night's finals against unbeaten Colgate, an 83-77 winner over Texas State in the first game. The Owls held a 2-point halftime lead before Jacobs sparked a second half rally with 13 points. Jacksonville State (1-2) held a 2-point lead with just under three minutes remaining before the Owls reeled off nine points in a row for a 79-72 lead. J.D. Pollock put the game away for Kennesaw State, making a pair of free throws with 15 seconds remaining. Stegall also led the Owls with 6 assists. Jonathan Whipple added 11 and Ryan Daugherty 10 for Kennesaw. Dorian Brown led Jacksonville (1-2) with 22 points, hitting 10 of 12 shots. J.J. Wesley added 15 for the Gamecocks, all on 3-pointers.
